{"parse":{"title":"Songs to Make the Dust Dance on the Beams","pageid":20740724,"revid":798298595,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <i><b>Ry\u014djin Hish\u014d</b></i><span style=\"font-weight: normal\">&#32;(<span lang=\"ja\">\u6881\u5875\u79d8\u6284</span>, <i>Songs to Make the Dust Dance on the Beams</i>)</span> is an anthology of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_poetry#Poetry_in_the_period_of_cloistered_rule\" title=\"Japanese poetry\">imay\u014d</a></i> \u4eca\u69d8 songs. Originally it consisted of two collections joined together by <a href=\"/wiki/Cloistered_Emperor\" title=\"Cloistered Emperor\">Cloistered</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Emperor_Go-Shirakawa\" title=\"Emperor Go-Shirakawa\">Emperor Go-Shirakawa</a>: the <i>Kashish\u016b</i> \u6b4c\u8a5e\u96c6 and the <i>Kudensh\u016b</i> \u53e3\u4f1d\u96c6. The works were probably from the repertoire of the Emperor's tutor, the aged singer <a href=\"/wiki/Otomae\" title=\"Otomae\">Otomae</a>, whose superlative mastery of the art derived from four generations of teachers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Only a fragment (about 10%) of this work is still extant.\nThese songs were very popular in the 12th century <a href=\"/wiki/Japan\" title=\"Japan\">Japan</a>, but quickly fell into disuse in the <a href=\"/wiki/Kamakura_period\" title=\"Kamakura period\">Kamakura period</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Songs_to_Make_the_Dust_Dance_on_the_Beams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFYung-Hee_Kim1994\" class=\"citation\">Yung-Hee Kim (1994), <i>Songs to Make the Dust Dance: The Ry\u014djin Hish\u014d of Twelfth-century Japan</i>, University of California Press, pp.&#160;19\u201320, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780520080669\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780520080669\">9780520080669</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Songs+to+Make+the+Dust+Dance%3A+The+Ry%C5%8Djin+Hish%C5%8D+of+Twelfth-century+Japan&amp;rft.pages=19-20&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=9780520080669&amp;rft.au=Yung-Hee+Kim&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASongs+to+Make+the+Dust+Dance+on+the+Beams\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFJ._Michele_Edwards2001\" class=\"citation\">J. Michele Edwards (2001), \"Women in Music to ca. 1450\",  in Karin Pendle, <i>Women &amp; Music: A History</i>, Indiana University Press, p.&#160;36, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780253338198\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780253338198\">9780253338198</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Women+in+Music+to+ca.+1450&amp;rft.btitle=Women+%26+Music%3A+A+History&amp;rft.pages=36&amp;rft.pub=Indiana+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=9780253338198&amp;rft.au=J.+Michele+Edwards&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASongs+to+Make+the+Dust+Dance+on+the+Beams\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Earl Roy Miner, Hiroko Odagiri, and Robert E. Morrell (1985). <i>The Princeton companion to classical Japanese literature.</i> Princeton, N.J.&#160;: Princeton University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-691-06599-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-691-06599-1\">978-0-691-06599-1</a> (p. 221).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Japanese_poetry\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Japanese_poetry\" title=\"Template:Japanese poetry\"><abbr title=\"View this template\" style=\"text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none; padding:0;\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Japanese_poetry\" title=\"Template talk:Japanese poetry\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\" style=\"text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none; padding:0;\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Japanese_poetry&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\" style=\"text-align:center;;;background:none t